Subject: Fix configure metadata lookup and PostgreSQL 14-18 compatibility

The upstream fork still carries stale references to the old columnar
layout in both configure metadata lookup and Makefile.global.in. Those
leave CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION empty during configure and make clean fail
by depending on a non-existent src/backend/columnar/columnar.control.

It also uses PG_VERSION_16/17/18 compatibility constants in multiple
files before including pg_version_constants.h. On older branches those
macros are undefined, so the preprocessor treats them as zero and can
take the wrong branch, breaking the build with errors such as:

  fatal error: commands/explain_format.h: No such file or directory

On PostgreSQL 14/15, rowcompress_tableam.c still assumes the newer
RelFileLocatorEquals helper, the post-PG16 TableAmRoutine callback name,
and transitive SysScanDesc declarations. Those old-branch API mismatches
break the EL9/RPM builds even though the rest of the source tree already
ships compatibility helpers for the same version range.

Point the stale control-file references at storage_engine.control, make
the version guards use pg_version_constants.h consistently, guard the
rowcompress ReadStream include, route parallel scan relfile lookups
through RelationPhysicalIdentifier_compat(), add the missing PG14/15
rowcompress compatibility shims, fix the stale rowcompress estimate-size
forward declaration, and keep `make clean` from failing when the
regression subdir does not implement `clean-regression`.
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -49,6 +49,6 @@
 	$(MAKE) -C src/test/regress check-all
 
 clean-regression:
-	$(MAKE) -C src/test/regress clean-regression
+	$(MAKE) -C src/test/regress clean-regression || true
 
 .PHONY: all check clean install install-all
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -2680,7 +2680,7 @@
 
 
 # CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION definition
-CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION="`grep '^default_version' $srcdir/src/backend/columnar/columnar.control | cut -d\' -f2`"
+CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION="`grep '^default_version' $srcdir/src/backend/engine/storage_engine.control | cut -d\' -f2`"
 
 printf "%s\n" "#define CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION \"$CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION\"" >>confdefs.h
 
--- a/configure.in
+++ b/configure.in
@@ -42,7 +42,7 @@
 AC_DEFINE_UNQUOTED(CITUS_VERSION_NUM, $CITUS_VERSION_NUM, [Citus version as a number])
 
 # CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION definition
-[CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION="`grep '^default_version' $srcdir/src/backend/columnar/columnar.control | cut -d\' -f2`"]
+[CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION="`grep '^default_version' $srcdir/src/backend/engine/storage_engine.control | cut -d\' -f2`"]
 AC_DEFINE_UNQUOTED([CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION], "$CITUS_EXTENSIONVERSION", [Extension version expected by this Citus build])
 
 # Re-check for flex. That allows to compile citus against a postgres
--- a/Makefile.global.in
+++ b/Makefile.global.in
@@ -61,7 +61,7 @@
 
